[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m going to show you how you can use Mirageedit to automatically generate and edit a UGC like video. Start by describing the video idea. My video is going to be about captions new generative model called Mirage. After that, Mirage starts gathering'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'information automatically about the video idea. Sometimes it may ask you for your product or service website link. Now you can customize the actor and the editing style. For the actor, you have'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'three options. Choosing an already generated actor from the actor library, generating a new actor based on shuffle prompts, or generating an AI clone of yourself with Mirage Twin. Your Mirage'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Twin is private and only visible to you. If you don\'t need an actor to be shown in your video, you can enable the voice over only option. You can also add additional media to use in the edit.'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'After confirming, Mirage prepares the script and audio for your video. You can tap the play button to preview the audio of your selected voice. For the voice, you can select an already generated'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'voice or generate an AI voice clone. Your AI voice clone is private and only accessible to you. Review the script for your video, make any final adjustments, and then tap on generate.'
